12/07/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Kurdish terrorists killed two Turkish police officers and injured two others on Tuesday (11 July). 
According to official reports, members of the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) gunned down the plainclothes officers on a street in a small town near the Iraqi border. 
They then opened fire on patrols that raced to the scene of the incident. 
The PKK has claimed responsibility for the attack. 
(Reuters - 11/07/06)
